sentences: Nina Elisabet Persson (audio ; born 6 September 1974) is the lead singer and lyricist for the Swedish rock band The Cardigans.
Persson made her acting debut in the film Om Gud vill which was released in 2006.
She also features on the 2009 Sparklehorse/Danger Mouse collaboration Dark Night of the Soul singing "Daddy's Gone".

Persson was diagnosed with cervical cancer in 2009, and underwent surgical treatment.
After three attempts at in vitro fertilization, their son Nils was born on 30 September 2010.
For several years the family resided in Harlem, New York City, but in 2015 they decided to relocate to Malmö, the former base of the Cardigans.
